<h1>News</h1>
<p>
<u>2011</u><br>
<p>
AquaSAXS will be opened soon, a web-based software to calculate SAXS spectra from PDB coordinates,
including the solvent density predicted by AquaSol.
<p>
<u>
2010</u>
<p>
A meeting in I. Pasteur of the <a href=./programme_stanford_salles.pdf>France-Stanford Exchange Program</a> (September)<br>

<p>
<u>2009</u>
<p>
MinActionPath was updated (<a href=http://lorentz.dynstr.pasteur.fr/joel/traj_newpath_submission.php>NewPath</a>) to accept up to 10,000 atoms thanks to Patrice Koehl (UC Davis, USA). 
<br>
<p>
<u>2008</u>
<p>
The  <a href=
http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2599837>dipolar solvent model</a> was described in Biophysical Journal (coll. H. Orland).
<p>
<p>
<u>2007</u>
<p>
<a href="http://lorentz.immstr.pasteur.fr/joel/index.php">
MinActionPath web server</a>: Generate the most probable trajectory between two known structural forms
of the same macromolecule (J. Franklin).
<br>
<p>
<u>2006</u>
<p>
